HOUSE BILL 23
R2 6lr1439
(PRE–FILED)
By: Delegate Woods
Requested: October 29, 2025
Introduced and read first time: January 14, 2026
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Motor Vehicle Administration – Identification Cards – Issuance to Minors
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the Motor Vehicle Administration from requiring a parent
4 or legal guardian of a minor at least a certain age to cosign or be present at the time
5 of submission of the minor’s application for an identification card; requiring the
6 Administration to adopt regulations establishing acceptable forms of documentation
7 establishing proof of residency that a minor at least a certain age may use in an
8 application for an identification card; and generally relating to State–issued
9 identification cards for minors.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
11 Article – Transportation
12 Section 12–301(a)
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Transportation
18 12–301.
19 (a) (1) On application, the Administration shall issue an identification card to
20 any applicant who:
21 [(1)] (I) Is a resident of this State;
22 [(2)] (II) Does not have a driver’s license;
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb0023*

2 HOUSE BILL 23
1 [(3)] (III) Presents a birth certificate or other proof of age and identity
2 acceptable to the Administration;
3 [(4)] (IV) Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that the applicant
4 has lawful status;
5 [(5) (i)] (V) 1. Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that
6 the applicant has a valid Social Security number by presenting the applicant’s Social
7 Security Administration account card or, if the Social Security Administration account card
8 is not available, any of the following documents bearing the applicant’s Social Security
9 number:
10 [1.] A. A current W–2 form;
11 [2.] B. A current SSA–1099 form;
12 [3.] C. A current non–SSA–1099 form; or
13 [4.] D. A current pay stub with the applicant’s name and
14 Social Security number on it; or
15 [(ii)] 2. Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that the
16 applicant is not eligible for a Social Security number; and
17 [(6)] (VI) Presents a completed application for an identification card on a
18 form furnished by the Administration.
19 (2) THE ADMINISTRATION MAY NOT REQUIRE A PARENT OR LEGAL
20 GUARDIAN OF A MINOR AT LEAST 15 YEARS OF AGE TO COSIGN OR BE PRESENT AT
21 THE TIME OF SUBMISSION OF THE MINOR’S APPLICATION FOR AN IDENTIFICATION
22 CARD.
23 (3) (I) THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS
24 ESTABLISHING ACCEPTABLE FORMS OF DOCUMENTATION ESTABLISHING PROOF OF
25 RESIDENCY THAT A MINOR AT LEAST 15 YEARS OF AGE MAY USE IN AN APPLICATION
26 FOR AN IDENTIFICATION CARD, INCLUDING:
27 1. SCHOOL ENROLLMENT RECORDS, REPORT CARDS, OR
28 TRANSCRIPTS ISSUED BY A PUBLIC OR PRIVATE SCHOOL;
29 2. DOCUMENTATION FROM A HOMELESS SERVICES
30 PROVIDER, SHELTER, OR SOCIAL SERVICES AGENCY THAT VERIFIES RESIDENCY;
31 3. COURT DOCUMENTS;

HOUSE BILL 23 3
1 4. CHILD WELFARE AGENCY RECORDS;
2 5. HEALTH INSURANCE DOCUMENTS;
3 6. IF ACCOMPANIED BY SUFFICIENT DOCUMENTATION
4 ESTABLISHING PROOF OF THE ADULT’S RESIDENCE, A NOTARIZED AFFIDAVIT
5 SIGNED BY AN ADULT WITH WHOM THE MINOR RESIDES ATTESTING TO THE MINOR’S
6 RESIDENCY; OR
7 7. ANY OTHER DOCUMENT THAT THE ADMINISTRATION
8 DETERMINES APPROPRIATE.
9 (II) IF A MINOR AT LEAST 15 YEARS OF AGE IS UNABLE TO
10 PROVIDE DOCUMENTATION THAT SATISFIES THE REQUIREMENTS OF THE FEDERAL
11 REAL ID ACT, THE ADMINISTRATION MAY ISSUE AN IDENTIFICATION CARD THAT
12 IS NOT COMPLIANT WITH THE FEDERAL REAL ID ACT.
13 (III) THIS PARAGRAPH MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO LIMIT THE
14 ADMINISTRATION’S AUTHORITY TO REQUIRE DOCUMENTATION NECESSARY TO
15 COMPLY WITH THE REQUIREMENTS OF THE FEDERAL REAL ID ACT, INCLUDING
16 DOCUMENTATION ESTABLISHING PROOF OF RESIDENCY.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
18 October 1, 2026.

